subSubSection.paragraph:
Rhinolophus affinis
(non Horsf.) Thomas, Ann. Mus. Civ. Genova

Diagnosis. Similar to
Rh. sumatranus ,
but horse-shoe much broader: 0 ’ 2 mm.; ears longer and much broader. Forearm 52-52 ’ 3 mm.

caption.paragraph:
Measurements of
Rh. acuminatus ,
sumatranus ,
and
calypso .

subSubSection.paragraph:
Colour. ♂ ad. and ♀ ad., in alcohol, unfaded; teeth unworn. As
Rh. refulgens .

Skull. As in
Rh. sumatranus ,
but maxiliar width, across the antero-external corners of in1, narrower (8 ’ 1 mm., as against 8'6 in Rh. szbmatranus).

Dentition. Essentially as in
Rh. sumatranus ,
but the interspace between the upper canine and p4 broader; p3 and pt not quite in contact.
